Main Components

Frame
5v to 400kv DC converter
Li-ion battery 18650
copper wire emitter
Copper ring *Copper Tube
DIY test stand
some gloves
Assembly Overview
Use strands of copper wire to form the emitter needle.

Mount the emitter outside the frame.

Install the copper tube around the outer outer electroplated tube.

Connect the emmiter wire to the transformer

Battery ---> Tranformer
Transfoermer ---> emitter needle
Emitter ---> Conducting module
Mount the thruster** on a diy test stand using insulating materials.

Insulate all exposed HV connections** with silicone or hot glue.(OPTIONAL :) JK )

Testing
Turn on the system and check for a faint corona glow.
Use lightweight objects to observe airflow.
A helium balloon can be used to visualize the generated thrust.
Typical thrust is only a few grams-force, suitable for demonstrations
